<bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
<head>Biographical Information
</head>
<p>Mary H. Land (1859-1963) was born in White Marsh, Surry County to Henry Carter Land and Mary R. Marable Land (1831-1925). In 1887, Mary H. Land married Private Nicholas C. Wright (1842-1894). The Wrights co-owned and managed a general store in Surry County until Nicholas Wright's death in January 1894. In August 1894, Mary L. Wright had a son, whom she named Nicholas Carter Wright (1894-1958) after his late father. Following her husband's death, Mary L. Wright become the sole owner of the store, and managed it at least until 1900.
</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
<head>Scope and Content
</head>
<p>Papers, 1876-1919, of Mary L. Wright consist of correspondence, advertisements, price lists, receipts, invoices, and contracts related to the management of the Wright's unnamed general store. Collection also includes several miscellaneous art prints and notes. 
</p>
</scopecontent>

