<scopecontent>
<p>Correspondence, 1887-1919, is primarily comprised of letters from merchants and advertisers addressed to Mary L. Wright, in regards to the Wrights' general store. Topics include the announcement and advertisement of new merchandise, as well as from merchants seeking payment for goods bought by Mary L. Wright for her store. The majority of the correspondence comes from Virginia, though many letters originate in Baltimore, Maryland. Also included is a folder of undated and empty envelopes addressed to Mrs. N.C. Wright. 
</p>
</scopecontent>

